rap JSON.parse in try/catch, return 400 with {error:'invalid_json'} before outer handler.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"severity\\\": \\\"low\\\",\\n      \\\"issue\\\": \\\"app.js relies on innerHTML string concatenation for dynamic UI, risking XSS if escapeHtml misses edge cases.\\\",\\n      \\\"fix\\\": \\\"Adopt document.createElement or DOMPurify for detail panel rendering to guarantee safe DOM insertion.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"severity\\\": \\\"medium\\\",\\n      \\\"issue\\\": \\\"ingest.js addCustomApp mixes sync loadApps with async refreshApps fallback, risking race conditions on concurrent calls.\\\",\\n      \\\"fix\\\": \\\"Convert loadApps to async or implement a mutex/queue to serialize state mutations during refresh.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"suggested_next_steps\\\": [\\n    \\\"Integrate OpenRouter fanout for automated review theme extraction\\\",\\n    \\\"Add Qlty and Promptfoo gates to CI pipeline\\\",\\n    \\\"Implement live-smoke mode with actual Apify tokens and rate limiting\\\",\\n    \\\"Add response caching and pagination for /api/apps endpoint\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\n./reports/consumer-radar/reviews/kimi-feedback.json:9:  \"raw_excerpt\": \"The user wants me to review a generated Consumer App Radar app based on provided source excerpts and file list. I need to return compact JSON only with specific fields: verdict, score, findings (max 3, severity/issue/fix under 180 chars), and suggested_next_steps.\\n\\nLet me analyze the source excerpts carefully:\\n\\n1. **package.json**: Standard setup, scripts include start, dev, test, typecheck, build. No dependencies. Uses node --check for syntax checking. Tests use node --test.\\n\\n2. **README.md**: Mentions fixture data for CI, live adapters scaffolded. Port 4317.\\n\\n3. **src/server.js**: \\n   - Uses node:http, node:fs, node:path\\n   - Endpoints: /health, /api/summary (GET), /api/apps (GET), /api/apps (POST), /api/apps/:id (GET), /api/refresh (POST)\\n   - Static file serving with basic path traversal protection (`!file.startsWith(publicDir)`)\\n   - CORS header on JSON responses\\n   - Error handling with try/catch\\n   - Calls refreshApps({ mode: \\\"fixture\\\" }) on startup\\n   - Port from env or 4317\\n\\n4. **src/ingest.js**:\\n   - Loads fixtures from ../fixtures/apps.json\\n   - Allowed modes: \\\"fixture\\\", \\\"live-smoke\\\"\\n   - refreshApps loads fixture apps and ranks them\\n   - addCustomApp creates seed data w\",\n./workflows/factory/goal-to-production.fabro:120:        script=\"ROOT='{{ inputs.app_dir|default('apps/generated-from-goal') }}'; test -d \\\"$ROOT\\\"; mkdir -p .maestro/factory; find \\\"$ROOT\\\" -path '*/node_modules' -prune -o \\\\( -name package.json -o -name Cargo.toml \\\\) -print | sort > .maestro/factory/project-manifests.txt; test -s .maestro/factory/project-manifests.txt; while IFS= read -r manifest; do dir=$(dirname \\\"$manifest\\\"); name=$(basename \\\"$manifest\\\"); if [ \\\"$name\\\" = package.json ]; then (cd \\\"$dir\\\"; if [ ! -d node_modules ]; then npm install; fi; npm run typecheck --if-present; npm test --if-present; npm run build --if-present); elif [ \\\"$name\\\" = Cargo.toml ]; then (cd \\\"$dir\\\"; cargo fmt --check && cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --workspace); fi; done < .maestro/factory/project-manifests.txt; printf '# CI Report\\\\n\\\\nnative_checks=ok\\\\n' > .maestro/factory/ci-report.md\"\n./workflows/factory/goal-to-production.fabro:164:        label=\"CI/CD Gate\",\n./reports/consumer-radar/reviews/deepseek-feedback.json:15:        \"fix\": \"Add Qlty and Promptfoo scripts in CI if available; otherwise document fallback.\"\n./reports/consumer-radar/reviews/deepseek-feedback.json:29:  \"raw_excerpt\": \"{\\n  \\\"verdict\\\": \\\"APPROVE\\\",\\n  \\\"score\\\": 0.95,\\n  \\\"findings\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"severity\\\": \\\"low\\\",\\n      \\\"issue\\\": \\\"Qlty and Promptfoo gates not integrated; spec requires them but fallback to native checks is acceptable for spike.\\\",\\n      \\\"fix\\\": \\\"Add Qlty and Promptfoo scripts in CI if available; otherwise document fallback.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"severity\\\": \\\"low\\\",\\n      \\\"issue\\\": \\\"Client-side app.js excerpt truncated; full rendering logic not fully verifiable but structure matches spec.\\\",\\n      \\\"fix\\\": \\\"Complete client-side code review if needed; current implementation appears functional.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"suggested_next_steps\\\": [\\n    \\\"Run full test suite and typecheck to confirm no runtime errors.\\\",\\n    \\\"Add Qlty and Promptfoo integration for production readiness.\\\",\\n    \\\"Expand test coverage for API endpoints and edge cases.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\n./reports/consumer-radar/quality/promptfoo-report.json:7:  \"promptfoo_stdout_excerpt\": \"                │ growth signals, social strategy,       │\\n│                                        │                                        │ review themes, and feature requests.   │\\n│                                        │                                        │ Fixture JSON:                          │\\n│                                        │                                        │ {{apps_fixture}}                       │\\n│                                        │                                        │ Re...                                  │\\n├────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\\n│ file://../apps/generated-consumer-app… │ growth signals, social strategy,       │ [PASS] ```json                         │\\n│                                        │ review themes, feature requests        │ {                                      │\\n│                                        │                                        │   \\\"verdict\\\": \\\"APPROVE\\\",                │\\n│                                        │   