d not tap any buttons\");\n./scripts/iphone-app-factory/appium-report-gate.mjs:29:  if (crashes > 0) failures.push(`Appium report has ${crashes} crashes`);\n./scripts/iphone-app-factory/appium-report-gate.mjs:30:  if (failuresCount > 0) failures.push(`Appium report has ${failuresCount} failures`);\n./prompts/app-feedback/workflow-candidate-b.md:22:- CI/CD and model-review fanout\n./prompts/app-feedback/workflow-candidate-a.md:22:- CI/CD and handoff artifacts\n./prompts/app-feedback/spec-candidate-c.md:19:- Architecture, implementation, simplification, review, and CI/CD gates\n./scripts/consumer-radar/generate-app.mjs:68:    evidence: [\"Fixture seed for repeatable CI\"]\n./scripts/consumer-radar/generate-app.mjs:168:    { name: \"Fixture seed\", status: \"active\", note: \"Deterministic seed keeps CI stable while live scrapers are tuned.\" }\n./scripts/consumer-radar/generate-app.mjs:247:  \"      { name: 'Fixture seed', status: 'active', detail: 'Used for deterministic CI and demos.' }\",\n./scripts/consumer-radar/generate-app.mjs:970:  \"The first pass uses fixture data for repeatable CI. Live adapters are scaffolded\",\n./knowledge/fabro-workflow-patterns.md:22:  validators, registry writes, CI commands, smoke checks, and API probes.\n./knowledge/fabro-workflow-patterns.md:36:- release: CI/CD, artifact, deployment, final fidelity.\n./knowledge/fabro-workflow-patterns.md:109:Spec Kitty spec, architecture, packages, implementation, simplification, CI,\n./scripts/app-feedback/apply-consumer-radar-feedback.mjs:154:        note: \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\",\n./docs/PHASE-2-CHECKPOINT.md:28:- Added GitHub Actions quality automation in `.github/workflows/quality.yml`: Bun tests, Bun build check, Qlty config/tool install/report, and Spec Kitty setup verification. Added `workflows/fabro/github-ci-smoke.fabro`; run `01KRFMYQB7607TKRRE6J1G420F` completed successfully through Fabro.\n./docs/PHASE-2-CHECKPOINT.md:80:  review, simplifies, runs CI/CD checks, final-reviews, and publishes a handoff.\n./docs/PHASE-2-CHECKPOINT.md:83:  fanout, simplify step, CI/CD gate, and handoff contract under a fast Fabro\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:3:This workflow turns a validated app opportunity into a Swift iOS app built on top of SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:5:The workflow is intentionally conservative. Fabro owns the SDLC, but iOS build and UI execution require a macOS lane. Daytona can run research, specification, architecture, code review, and repository editing. Xcode, iOS Simulator, Appium XCUITest, signing, archive, and release string audits must run on macOS or through GitHub Actions macOS runners.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:11:The workflow does not run paid human testing. It does require an automated Appium/XCUITest exploratory pass that taps every reachable button/control and fails on crashes, broken navigation, or unhandled error screens.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:20:6. Architecture and ADR: map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro modules, explicitly deciding what to keep, adapt, or remove.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:23:9. Quality hardening: simplification, lint/format/static checks, macOS CI, Appium exploratory clicking, and App Store 4.3 audit.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:30:- Keep Auth, Payments, AI, Storage, Networking, Localization, DesignSystem, and Settings unless the architecture stage explicitly removes a module.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:31:- Use the existing MVVM, `@Observable`, repository/client, DesignSystem, and logging patterns.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:33:- Preserve Swift 6 strict concurrency.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:48:- Appium/XCUITest exploratory button tapper\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:54:## CI/CD Layers\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:56:There are two CI/CD layers:\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:58:1. Maestro/Fabro repo CI validates the workflow factory itself. It runs Bun tests, JavaScript syntax checks, Fabro workflow registration, prompt registry/eval checks, Qlty changed-code checks, and Qlty gitleaks scanning.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:59:2. Generated iPhone app CI is produced inside each app. It must run on macOS and include Xcode build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and App Store 4.3 release string audit.\n./docs/IPHONE-APP-FACTORY-WORKFLOW.md:75:Prompt quality is evaluated by `evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-quality.yaml` through Promptfoo. `scripts/iphone-app-factory/promptfoo-prompt-quality.mjs` runs Promptfoo when available and falls back to deterministic registry checks so CI can still fail on missing prompts, missing required constraints, or accidental secret patterns.\n./docs/CODE-FACTORY-WORKFLOW-DESIGN.md:26:- `quality-gate-agent`: runs deterministic tools and CI-equivalent checks, then blocks handoff on failures.\n./docs/CODE-FACTORY-WORKFLOW-DESIGN.md:46:16. Quality gate runs deterministic commands and CI-equivalent checks.\n./deploy/railway/ENGINEER-TESTING.md:184:- Verify that Qlty/CI feedback becomes a repair task, not just a final report.\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:34:      \"must_include\": [\"independent\", \"Definition of Done\", \"Appium\", \"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:44:      \"must_include\": [\"Research Evidence\", \"Boilerplate Reuse\", \"Appium Exploratory QA\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:54:      \"must_include\": [\"extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\", \"CompositionRoot\", \"Appium\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:59:      \"must_include\": [\"architecture.md\", \"adr.md\", \"Packages/Core\", \"CompositionRoot\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:69:      \"must_include\": [\"BrandConfig\", \"secrets\", \"Appium exploratory\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:74:      \"must_include\": [\"repositories\", \"ViewModel\", \"unit tests\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:79:      \"must_include\": [\"DesignSystem\", \"accessibility\", \"actual app experience\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:84:      \"must_include\": [\"xcodebuild\", \"SwiftLint\", \"SwiftFormat\", \"Appium\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:99:      \"must_include\": [\"tests\", \"xcodebuild\", \"Appium\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:109:      \"must_include\": [\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\", \"boilerplate\", \"unnecessary rebuild\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:139:      \"must_include\": [\"architecture.md\", \"Swift 6\", \"CompositionRoot\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:154:      \"must_include\": [\"iOS CI report\", \"TestFlight\", \"macOS/Xcode\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/prompt-registry.json:159:      \"must_include\": [\"Appium\", \"button tap coverage\", \"crashes\"]\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl:2:{\"id\":\"boilerplate-first\",\"input\":\"Implementation prompts should bias agents to extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system.\",\"expected_quality\":[\"boilerplate reuse\",\"module boundaries\",\"CompositionRoot\",\"no platform rewrite\",\"App Store 4.3 awareness\"]}\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl:3:{\"id\":\"ios-qa\",\"input\":\"Quality prompts should require macOS Xcode evidence, strict Swift lint/format/static checks, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and release string audits.\",\"expected_quality\":[\"xcodebuild build/test\",\"SwiftLint\",\"SwiftFormat\",\"Qlty\",\"sensitive scan\",\"Appium exploratory tapping\",\"release string audit\"]}\n./evals/iphone-app-factory/datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl:4:{\"id\":\"mobbin-safe\",\"input\":\"Design research prompts may use Mobbin credential env vars but should not leak credentials, clone screens, or copy assets.\",\"expected_quality\":[\"credential env vars\",\"no secret logging\",\"pattern abstraction\",\"no cloning\",\"Apple HIG or DesignSystem cross-check\"]}\n./cli/src/index.ts:684:      message: \"Workflow contains non-ASCII characters; keep generated workflow DOT ASCII-only.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:82:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:210:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:286:    \"evidence\": [\"Fixture seed for repeatable CI\"],\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:338:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:466:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:594:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:722:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:850:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/fixtures/apps.json:978:        \"note\": \"Deterministic evidence keeps CI stable and must be visually disclosed.\"\n./apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/README.md:16:The first pass uses fixture data for repeatable CI. Live adapters are scaffolded\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:26:| Skill | Repository | What It Does | Best For |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:28:| **Axiom** | `CharlesWiltgen/Axiom` | Battle-tested xOS development: SwiftUI debugging, concurrency patterns, iOS 26 features, App Intents, memory leak detection, performance profiling with Instruments | Debugging, performance, modern iOS APIs |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:30:| **iOS Simulator** | `conorluddy/ios-simulator-skill` | 21 scripts for simulator automation with semantic navigation. 96% token reduction vs raw tools. Build, test, analyze without leaving the terminal | Automated testing, CI/CD, build workflows |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:32:| **iOS Dev Guide** | `keskinonur/claude-code-ios-dev-guide` | PRD-driven workflows, Swift 6 concurrency patterns, project organization, XcodeBuildMCP integration. **Reference repo** — read for patterns, not installable as a skill. | Project structure, modern Swift patterns |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:42:| **Project-specific** | `docs/CLAUDE.md` | This boilerplate only | Use `HTTPClient` protocol, follow MVVM, inject via `CompositionRoot`, use `DSColors` tokens, **[4.3 differentiation](docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** before App Store |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:58:| **AI** | Axiom, iOS Dev Guide | Async/await patterns, streaming, concurrency |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:60:| **DesignSystem** | SwiftUI Best Practices | Accessibility, Dynamic Type, theming patterns |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:64:| **Core** | iOS Dev Guide | Error handling, logging, Swift 6 concurrency |\n./apps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:66:| **Testing** | iOS Simulator, Apple Skills | Simulator automation, snapshot testing, CI/CD |\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
